1. Project Overview

Objective:

Implement a Linux server monitoring system.

Automate system backups.

Secure the server using SSH hardening and firewall.

Tools Used:

Ubuntu VM

Bash scripting

Cron jobs & systemd services

UFW firewall

Key Features:

System health monitoring (CPU, memory, disk, processes)

Automated daily backups with retention policy

Systemd service for monitoring

SSH hardening & firewall security

2. Architecture Diagram
User (SSH)
   |
   v
Ubuntu VM
   |
-----------------------------------------
| System Monitor | Backup Script | Logs  |
-----------------------------------------
   |
Systemd Service / Cron Jobs
   |
   v
/var/log or /root/logs, /backup


Monitoring script writes to /root/system_monitor.log

Backup script writes to /backup with retention policy

Cron jobs handle automation

systemd service ensures monitoring runs safely

3. Step-by-Step Implementation
STEP 1: Linux Monitoring Script

Location: /project_data/system_monitor.sh

#!/bin/bash
echo "===== System Health Report ====="
echo "Date: $(date)"

echo "CPU Load:"
uptime

echo "Memory Usage:"
free -h

echo "Disk Usage:"
df -h

echo "Top Processes:"
ps -eo pid,ppid,cmd,%mem,%cpu --sort=-%cpu | head


Make executable:

chmod +x /project_data/system_monitor.sh


Test manually:

/project_data/system_monitor.sh >> /root/system_monitor.log 2>&1
tail /root/system_monitor.log

STEP 2: Automate with Cron
crontab -e


Add:

*/30 * * * * /project_data/system_monitor.sh >> /root/system_monitor.log 2>&1


Runs every 30 minutes

Uses absolute path (cron-safe)

STEP 3: Automated Backup System

Backup Script: /project_data/backup.sh

#!/bin/bash
DATE=$(date +%F)
LOGFILE=/backup/backup.log

echo "===== Backup Started: $(date) =====" >> $LOGFILE
tar -czf /backup/home_backup_$DATE.tar.gz /home >> $LOGFILE 2>&1
find /backup -type f -name "*.tar.gz" -mtime +7 -delete
echo "===== Backup Completed: $(date) =====" >> $LOGFILE
echo "" >> $LOGFILE


Make executable:

chmod +x /project_data/backup.sh


Cron job (daily at 2 AM):

0 2 * * * /project_data/backup.sh

STEP 4: Systemd Service

Service File: /etc/systemd/system/system_monitor.service

[Unit]
Description=System Monitoring Service
After=network.target

[Service]
Type=oneshot
ExecStart=/project_data/system_monitor.sh

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target


Reload systemd:

systemctl daemon-reload
systemctl enable system_monitor
systemctl start system_monitor
systemctl status system_monitor

STEP 5: Security Hardening

Disable root login:

nano /etc/ssh/sshd_config
PermitRootLogin no
systemctl restart ssh


Enable firewall:

ufw allow ssh
ufw enable
ufw status verbose

4. Logs & Testing

Monitoring logs: /root/system_monitor.log

Backup logs: /backup/backup.log

Firewall: ufw status verbose

Cron logs: /var/log/syslog | grep CRON

5. Resume-Ready Achievements

Automated Linux system monitoring and backups

Secured server with SSH hardening and UFW

Implemented cron jobs and systemd service for automation

Managed log rotation and retention

6. Project Diagrams

System Flow:

